&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;All of the above.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Balthar Soil&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It is &lt;strong&gt;less fertile&lt;/strong&gt; and has &lt;strong&gt;less water absorption capacity.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Major crops that grow in such soil are &lt;strong&gt;Jowar, Bajra, and Gram.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It is found in&lt;strong&gt; Kaimur Plateau to Raj Mahal hills in the narrow belt&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Red and Yellow Soil&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;​This soil is formed from the &lt;strong&gt;disintegration of igneous and metamorphosed rocks&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;They are &lt;strong&gt;less fertile and thus suitable for coarse crops and pulses&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It is found in &lt;strong&gt;Banka, Gaya, Aurangabad, Jamui and Munger.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Red Sandy Soil&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;​&lt;/strong&gt;This soil has a&lt;strong&gt; higher percentage of sand&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It is&lt;strong&gt; less fertile and suitable for Bajra and Jowar Crops.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Bihar is located in the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;eastern region of India.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It is an&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;entirely land-locked state.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Bihar shares geographical boundaries with
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;West Bengal in the east.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Uttar Pradesh in the west.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Jharkhand in the South.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It also shares an&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;international border in the north with Nepal.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Malacca Strait&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Malacca Strait&lt;/span&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The Strait of Malacca connects the&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Andaman Sea (Indian Ocean) and the South China Sea (Pacific Ocean).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Stretching about&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;800km, it is the longest straits in the world&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;and facilitates not just shipping and the movement of people in the surrounding communities but is a confluence of trade, cultures, ideas, and knowledge between the East and West.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It runs between the&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Indonesian island of Sumatra to the west and peninsular (West) Malaysia and extreme southern Thailand&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;to the east and has an area of about&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;25,000 square miles (65,000 square km).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Singapore, one of the world&amp;rsquo;s most important ports, is situated at the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;strait&amp;rsquo;s southern end.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The global shift in economic power from the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;West to the East coupled with burgeoning trade, investments, and production in areas spanning the Indian and Pacific Ocean regions has given increasing importance to this region.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;//storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/22/01/61cd62f99a0942b48d96c7f7_16415355377711.png&quot; style=&quot;height: 408px; width: 350px;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Article 72&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(32, 33, 36);  &quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Article 72&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(32, 33, 36);  &quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;​&lt;/strong&gt;The&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;b style=&quot;color: rgb(32, 33, 36);  &quot;&gt;President&lt;/b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(32, 33, 36);  &quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;shall have the&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;b style=&quot;color: rgb(32, 33, 36);  &quot;&gt;power&lt;/b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(32, 33, 36);  &quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;to grant&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;b style=&quot;color: rgb(32, 33, 36);  &quot;&gt;pardons&lt;/b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(32, 33, 36);  &quot;&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;reprieves, respites, or remissions of punishment &lt;/strong&gt;or to suspend, remit or commute the sentence of any person convicted of any offense.&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;
		&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Article 72 &lt;/strong&gt;of the Indian Constitution deals &lt;strong&gt;with the pardoning powers of the President of India&lt;/strong&gt;. When the President of India takes an action over the case of punishment or the sentence of any person convicted for an offense, it takes the form of his pardoning powers.&lt;strong&gt; They are of five types&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;
			&lt;div&gt;Pardon&lt;/div&gt;
			&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;
			&lt;div&gt;Reprieve&lt;/div&gt;
			&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;
			&lt;div&gt;Remit&lt;/div&gt;
			&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;
			&lt;div&gt;Respite&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
			&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;
			&lt;div&gt;Commute&lt;/div&gt;
			&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;
&lt;table border=&quot;1&quot; cellpadding=&quot;1&quot; cellspacing=&quot;1&quot; style=&quot;width:350px;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;tbody&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Type&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Details&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pardon&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;When the President pardons,&lt;strong&gt; both the sentence and the conviction&lt;/strong&gt; of the convict completely absolve the sentences, punishments, and disqualifications&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Reprieve&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;When the President uses the pardoning power of &amp;lsquo;Respite&amp;rsquo;, he &lt;strong&gt;chooses to award a lesser sentence&lt;/strong&gt; in place of one originally awarded to the convict. For example, due to some special fact, such as the physical disability of a convict or the pregnancy of a woman offender, the President can use this power&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Remit&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;When the President chooses the pardoning power of &amp;lsquo;Reprieve&amp;rsquo;; &lt;strong&gt;he stays the execution of a sentence (especially that of death) for a temporary period&lt;/strong&gt;. By doing this, he enables the convict to have time to seek pardon or commutation from him&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Respite&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;When the President chooses the pardoning power of Remit, he acts to &lt;strong&gt;reduce the period of the sentence but the character of the sentence remains the same&lt;/strong&gt;. For example, a sentence of rigorous imprisonment for two years may be remitted to rigorous imprisonment for one year but the imprisonment remains rigorous&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Commute&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;When the President chooses to use this pardoning power of &amp;lsquo;Commute; he &lt;strong&gt;substitutes one form of punishment for a lighter form&lt;/strong&gt;. For example, a death sentence may be commuted to rigorous imprisonment, which in turn may be commuted to simple imprisonment.&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
	&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;u style=&quot;font-size: 21px; font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

